⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Newspeak
node 1984 · 1984 · ⟦Newspeak:1984:bdeb00⟧

WHO   — Newspeak — language as the cage
WHAT  — The ultimate censorship: not of speech but of thought, by deleting the very words freedom and rebellion would need.
WHERE — 1984 · 1984  Framework inputs: Nineteen Eighty-Four (George Orwell, 1949)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because Orwell's deepest fear is the dictionary — a mind that cannot form the idea it is forbidden to have.
HOW   — By cutting words, collapsing nuance (‘ungood’ for bad), and aiming at a tongue in which dissent is literally unsayable.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Cut the word and you cut the thought — when the last term for freedom is deleted, no one will ever be able to miss it.

spoken token : ston-kyx-rurn   ·   hex : bdeb00
